        <p class="intro">Below are things that inspire me. I hope this can help you understand me better. My passions include <a href="influences#entrepreneurship">Entrepreneurship</a>, <a href="influences#technology">Technology</a>, <a href="influences#ucd">User-Centered Design</a>, <a href="influences#sf">Science Fiction</a>, and the <a href="influences#outdoors">Outdoors</a>.</p>

        <h2 id="entrepreneurship">Entrepreneurship</h2>
        <p>I want to create my own startup, it's just a matter of time! My first introduction to entrepreneurship was Guy Kawasaki and his book The Art of the Start. But when I moved to San Francisco, everything changed; I was part of a real startup. I learned a lot from the inside. Since then, I read a lot of articles, and dream big! Paul Graham influenced me a lot. I loved Sam Altman's How to Start a Startup course at Stanford.</p>

